### Description

The application would allow housemates to schedule and reserve resources (like the kitchen or the washer/dryer) that can be used in a shared home such as student accommodation. 

---

### Description of the Data Model

A group of housemates living in shared accommodation want a system that allows them to schedule and reserve shared household resources such as kitchens, bathrooms, laundry machines, appliances, the TV, and more. These resources are often in high demand during certain times, and the housemates need a fair and organised way to manage access to the resources. The application stores information about the people using the system, the houses they belong to, the resources available in each house, the bookings made for those resources, and the expenses shared among housemates.

A user represents a person living in a shared home. Each user has a unique email, a name, and a password. A user belongs to 0 to many houses, and each house must have 1 to many users (many‑to‑many relationship). Users also create bookings for resources, and a user may have many bookings over time. A house has one user who is the admin, the admin manages the users association to a house.

A house represents a shared living unit such as an apartment or student housing. Each house has a unique address and a name. A house contains the resources that its residents can reserve. A house may have zero to many resources associated with it and a resource is associated to exactly one house (Note: While a typical house must have at least some resources. The resources we are concerned with here are the shared resources, hence the participation constraint is optional. )

A resource represents a reservable item within a house, such as a kitchen, bathroom, laundry machines, TV, or appliances or any other custom resource that is defined by the users. Each resource has a unique identifier and a name, and it belongs to exactly one house. A resource may have many bookings. A resource has a time limit which specifies the maximum allowed booking duration for that resource type, and an icon to identify the resource in the user interface. A resource may be further classified as either a space or an appliance in addition to any resource that a user wants to add. 

A space is a subtype of resource that represents a reservable area within a house, such as a kitchen, bathroom, or game room. In addition to the attributes inherited from resource, a space has an indicator that determines if the space requires cleaning after use, and an count specifying the maximum number of users that can share the space at a time.

An appliance is a subtype of resource that represents a reservable device within a house, such as a washer, dryer, microwave, or TV. In addition to the attributes inherited from resource, an appliance has a conditional indicating whether it requires maintenance after every use.

A booking represents a reservation made by a user for a specific resource. Each booking has a unique identifier, a start time, and an end time. A booking is scheduled by exactly one user while a user can have one to many bookings. A booking is associated with exactly one resource and a resource has one to many bookings.

A reminder is a notification associated with a booking. Each reminder has a reminder time, status of the reminder, and a message sent along with the reminder. A reminder depends on the existence of its associated booking. A booking may have zero to many reminders. 

An expense represents a cost that a user wants to split among housemates. Each expense has a total amount, a description, a creation date, a due date, a file path for an attached bill or receipt, and an indicator that denotes it as a recurring expense. An expense is created by exactly one user, and a user may create many expenses. A combination of the amount, description and the due date may be used as a unique identifier for the expense. An expense may be split among one to many users, and a user may be associated with one to many expenses. Everytime an expense is split among users, each housemates share of the expense is recorded and the payment status is maintained for this expense.

