### User Interaction Flow

- User signs up or logs in.
- Upon login, the **HouseListView** displays all houses associated with the user.
- User may:

    - Create a new house (becoming its admin), or
    - Select an existing house to view its resources.

- Within a house, the user can:

    - View resources
    - Add new resources (if admin). When adding a resource, the user may optionally classify it as a Space (providing a cleaning requirement and max occupancy) or an Appliance (providing a maintenance requirement).
    - Add new members by entering their username (admin only)
    - View and manage Expenses for the house

- Selecting a resource opens the **Resource Booking** screen.
- User creates a booking for the selected resource.

- After creating a booking, the user may add one or more Reminders for that booking by specifying a reminder time and message.

- User may view all their bookings in the **Bookings** screen. From here the user can also view, add, or delete reminders on any of their bookings.
- User may navigate to the Expenses screen to:

    - View all expenses they are associated with
    - Create a new expense, specifying the amount, description, due date, whether it is recurring, and optionally attaching a receipt
    - Split an expense among one or more housemates, recording each person's share
    - Mark their share of an expense as paid

- The **Profile** screen displays user information and includes a logout option.

